===Noun===
'''bastard''' (''plural:'' [[bastards]])

# An [[illegitimate]] child, previously used as a title (as in ''William the Bastard'').
# ''(often considered moderately vulgar: more frequently used to refer to a man)'' '''1.''' A wrong-doer; a sod. '''2.''' A contemptible or spiteful person.
# A coarse-grade steel file.

